<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA General Task//EN" "generalTask.dtd">
<task id="task_ylb_f1s_5q">
    <title>Stopping Pipelines</title>
    <shortdesc>Stop pipelines when you want <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> to
        stop processing data for the pipelines.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p><indexterm>pipelines<indexterm>stopping</indexterm></indexterm>When <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> runs a pipeline, it displays in the <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> console in Monitor mode by default. </p>
        </context>
        <steps id="steps_zjh_4bs_5q">
            <step>
                <cmd>From the <wintitle>Home</wintitle> page, select the pipelines in the list and
                    then click the <uicontrol>Stop</uicontrol> icon. Or to stop a pipeline in the
                    pipeline canvas, click the <uicontrol>Stop</uicontrol> icon.</cmd>
                <info>The <wintitle>Stop Pipeline Confirmation</wintitle> dialog box appears.</info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd> To stop the pipelines, click <uicontrol>Yes</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
